==English==
{{wikipedia|Exclusive disjunction}}
===Etymology===
From "[[exclusive]]" + "[[or]]", contrasting it with ''[[inclusive or]]''.

===Conjunction===
'''exclusive or'''

# {{cattag|logic|computing}} A [[connective]] joining two [[predicate]]s in [[exclusive disjunction]], i.e. one evaluating to true only when exactly one of its predicates is true.
:''false '''exclusive or''' false is false''
:''false '''exclusive or''' true is true''

